1. Start with creating a folder using the following command:
faas-cli new sleep --lang node12

2. Write the function

3. Build the function to a docker file using the cli tool
faas-cli build --filter "sleep" -f openFaaSFunctions.yml

4. Push the function to a docker repository with the cli tool. Be sure to be logged in to the docker cli tool.
faas-cli push --filter "sleep" -f openFaaSFunctions.yml